<p>Hey,</p>
<p>Sometimes I check HTTP responses with CURL so it would be great to format JSON responses.</p>
<p>There is cool <a target="_blank" href="https://stedolan.github.io/jq/">command line JSON parser</a> and you can pipe CURL output to it like that:</p>
<p><code>curl http://some.endpoint/with-json-response | jq '.'</code></p>
<p>I&rsquo;ve wrote useful function called <code>jcurl</code> that is basically wrapper on that command above:</p>
<pre tabindex="0"><code>function jcurl() {
 curl &#34;$@&#34; | jq &#39;.&#39;
}
</code></pre><br/>
<p>P.S.
Don&rsquo;t forget to source your <code>(bash|zsh|any)rc</code>.</p>